OL,6,F"The stamp itself is King Edward, so
OL,7,Fhe was king from 1901 until 1910, and
OL,8,Fyou could tell straight away from the
OL,9,Fhandwriting and the way it speaks,
OL,10,F'dearest, I could not', it was very
OL,11,Fmuch of the time.
OL,13,F"From what we can work out, the
OL,14,Fpostage stamp says August 3, 1903.
OL,15,FPencilled on the top it says
OL,16,FFishguard, Pembrokeshire, so we're
OL,17,Fwondering if it's come from Fishguard
OL,18,Fto Miss Lydia.
