OL,6,F"It's quite vague - the postcard. They
OL,7,Fare speaking of something they are
OL,8,Fboth aware of but don't want to reveal
OL,9,Fit on the postcard."
OL,11,FThe front of the postcard depicts a
OL,12,Fdrawing of a wintry scene with a stag
OL,13,Fin the foreground standing over a
OL,14,Ffrozen tree stump, with a body of
OL,15,Fwater and snowy mountains beyond, all
OL,16,Fbeneath a starry sky.
OL,18,FAt the top corner, the postcard reads:
OL,19,F"Remember me to Miss Gilbert + John
OL,20,Fwith love to all from (unreadable)".
